text.section:
Except as provided in subsections (d) and (e) of this section, after a disabled veteran dies, the surviving spouse of the disabled veteran shall receive a disabled veteran's property tax exemption:
for the dwelling house that was formerly owned by the disabled veteran:
if the dwelling house received an exemption under this section; and
if the surviving spouse owns and resides in the dwelling house;
for the dwelling house that was formerly occupied by the disabled veteran:
if the dwelling house did not receive an exemption under this section;
if the disabled veteran was domiciled in the State at death; and
if the surviving spouse owns and resides in the dwelling house; and
for a dwelling house subsequently acquired by the surviving spouse, equal to the exemption for the former dwelling house when the dwelling house owned by the surviving spouse was transferred by the surviving spouse:
if the surviving spouse owns and resides in the subsequently acquired dwelling house; and
if the surviving spouse has qualified under item (1) or (2) of this subsection.
